definition: to pluck (a string)/to play (a string instrument)/to spring or leap/to shoot (e.g. with a catapult)/(of cotton) to fluff or tease/to flick/to flip/to accuse/to impeach/elastic (of materials)
nature/character/property/quality/attribute/sexuality/sex/gender/suffix forming adjective from verb/suffix forming noun from adjective, corresponding to -ness or -ity/essence/CL:個|个[ge4]
capacity/quantity/amount/to estimate/abbr. for 量詞|量词[liang4 ci2], classifier (in Chinese grammar)/measure word

sentences.english: The first order non-simple harmonic coefficient enhances modulus.
sentences.chinese: 第一非簡諧係數的存在使彈性模量增大。

sentences.english: In a case study on the practical engineering, the elastic modulus and Poisson′s ratio are obtained.
sentences.chinese: 結合實際工程，反演了拱壩基岩的彈性模量和泊松比。

sentences.english: For identical shapes, the stiffness is proportional to the modulus of elasticity.
sentences.chinese: 對於同樣外形的材料，剛度與彈性模量是成比例的。

sentences.english: Some numerical examples are also given by assuming an exponential gradient function.
sentences.chinese: 對彈性模量按指數函數梯度變化的算例進行了分析。

sentences.english: The ferrule effect is influenced by elastic modulus of post and core materials.
sentences.chinese: 箍效應受樁核材料彈性模量的影響。

sentences.english: As an application, the scaling exponents of elastic modulus and loss modulus are also obtained.
sentences.chinese: 作爲應用，進而得到彈性模量和損耗模量的標度指數。

sentences.english: There is a parabola correlation between the MOE and vascular bundle proportion.
sentences.chinese: 抗彎彈性模量與維管束比量有較高的拋物線關係。
